org.apache.sling.jcr.ocm
Class OcmConstants

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.sling.jcr.ocm.OcmConstants

public class OcmConstants
extends Object

The OcmConstants interface provides constant values for event topics and event properties for events sent from this bundle.

Field Detail

RESOURCE_EVENT

public static final String RESOURCE_EVENT
The topic root for events published by this bundle (value is "org/apache/sling/jcr/ocm/OCMEvent"). Event consumers should register to "org/apache/sling/jcr/ocm/OCMEvent/*" to receive all events from this bundle.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

EVENT_MAPPING_ADDED

public static final String EVENT_MAPPING_ADDED
The name of the event sent after new Object Mappings have been registered (value is "org/apache/sling/jcr/ocm/OCMEvent/MAPPED").

Events of this topics have two additional properties: MAPPING_CLASS and MAPPING_NODE_TYPE.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

EVENT_MAPPING_REMOVED

public static final String EVENT_MAPPING_REMOVED
The name of the event sent after Object Mappings have been unregistered (value is "org/apache/sling/jcr/ocm/OCMEvent/UNMAPPED").

Events of this topics have two additional properties: MAPPING_CLASS and MAPPING_NODE_TYPE.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

MAPPING_CLASS

public static final String MAPPING_CLASS
The name of the event property providing a String[] of class names mapped at the time the event is sent (value is "MAPPED_CLASS"). This is the complete list of all classes which are supported by the content manager for mapping.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

MAPPING_NODE_TYPE

public static final String MAPPING_NODE_TYPE
The name of the event property providing a String[] of node types mapped at the time the event is sent (value is "MAPPED_NODE_TYPE"). This is the complete list of all node types which are supported by the content manager for mapping.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

MAPPER_BUNDLE_HEADER

The name of the bundle manifest header listing the bundle entries providing Object Content Mapping configurations (value is "Sling-Mappings").
